<h2>20.02.2006-24.02.2006
Uddannelse for Bæredygtig Udvikling på uddannelsesmessen didacta 2006 i Hannover i Tyskland.
</h2>
<div id="maincontenttext"><P>Messen vil være mødeplads for lærere og pædagoger. Messen er Europas største uddannelsesmesse med ca. 600 udstillere og forventet besøgstal på 65.000. Messen dækker hele uddannelsessektoren lige fra børnehave, skole, universitet, videreuddannelse. På messen vil Education Partnership Forum præsentere FN’s tiår for Uddannelse for Bæredygtig Udvikling. Det sker ved at UNESCO udvælger 20 projekter fra hele verden, der arbejder med ubu. Dette vil blive fulgt op af workshops og diskussionsrunder. Der vil desuden være et to timers TV-talkshow (fra 10-12 middag) med internationale gæster fra videnskab, kultur, samfund og politik-områderne. Emnet bliver “Intoxicated by Images. Is the Power of the Media also the Power of Education?” for at understrege, at et større og større antal mediekanaler (internetsider, aviser, tele og tv-tilbud) bestemmer hverdagen for mennesker over hele verden (siger Barbara Groth – talskvinde for SCHAU HIN!). De byder på en masse billeder, der konstant stiger – er kulturer holdt op med at tale, har eleverne mistet deres evne til at tale? Hvordan kan medierne sensibly støtte tiårets objektiver? I Tyskland støttes tiåret af Didacta Verband (Association) og forældre-informations-initiativet ”SCHAU HIN! Watch what your children are watching” sammen med Education Partnership Forum. Didacta Verband er en paraplyorganisation for virksomheder og organisationer, der leverer produkter og servicer til alle uddannelsessektorens dele – fra dagpleje/børnehave til skoler, højere uddannelsesinstitutioner og videreuddannelse. Er sponsor for uddannelsesmessen. SCHAU HIN! er et samarbejde mellem German Federal Ministry for Family Affairs, Senior Citizens, Women and Youth, telekommunikationsfirmaet Arcor, de offentlige tv-stationer ARD; ZDF og tv-magasinet TV Spielfilm. Kampagnen informerer og uddanner forældre og værger om range/rækken af elektroniske medier og hvordan man håndterer dem, kombineret med specifikke tips til opdragelsen/bringing up/opvækst af 3-13-årige. </P>
<P><BR>Currently Germany's northern and eastern states are engaged in important debates on cutting-edge educational policy and innovative ways of implementing new policy changes. didacta 2006 in Hannover will offer some important new ideas in this regard. Education professionals as well as parents and students can get a concise overview here of state-of-the-art educational and learning materials and the pedagogical techniques and approaches involved. <BR>An above-average percentage of education professionals in advisory and decision-making capacities take advantage of the superb conditions offered by this event to get a comprehensive overview of the entire education sector and its future evolution. In addition, over 80 percent of all visitors end up using products which they have viewed at the fair in their subsequent work. <BR>didacta 2006 in Hannover will also feature a series of discussions and debates, with a broad range of education policy talks, panel discussions, forums, workshops and continuing education events. These supporting events combine to make didacta Germany's biggest continuing education event for the education sector. So it is no surprise that numerous federal German states give teachers and educators a paid day off to visit the show. <BR>didacta 2006 in Hannover gives you a bird's-eye view of education: innovative products and services, discussions on all the latest issues and important new ideas for Germany's education landscape. Well-structured and clearly laid-out, this event appeals to exhibitors, education professionals and interested members of the public alike. <BR></P></div><!-- maincontenttext -->
